## CI/CD with GitHub Actions

### Setup

The GitHub Actions workflow is automatically included in your project at `.github/workflows/deploy-flyio.yml` when you select Fly.io as a deployment target.

1. Get your Fly.io API token:

```bash
fly auth token
```

2. Add the token to GitHub Secrets:
   - Go to Settings ‚Üí Secrets ‚Üí Actions
   - Add `FLY_API_TOKEN` with your token

### Features

The GitHub Actions workflow provides:

- **Automated Testing**: Runs tests on pull requests
- **Staging Deployment**: Auto-deploy to staging on merge to main
- **Production Deployment**: Deploy to production on merge to production branch
- **Preview Environments**: Creates preview apps for each pull request
- **Automatic Cleanup**: Removes preview apps when PRs are closed
- **Database Backups**: Creates backups before production deployments
- **Rollback on Failure**: Automatic rollback if deployment fails
- **Deployment Notifications**: Status updates on commits

### Deployment Workflow

```mermaid
graph LR
    PR[Pull Request] --> Test[Run Tests]
    Test --> Preview[Deploy Preview]

    Main[Merge to Main] --> Staging[Deploy Staging]

    Prod[Merge to Production] --> Backup[Backup DB]
    Backup --> Deploy[Deploy Production]
    Deploy --> Scale[Auto-scale]
```

